Technology - Platform
Function
Candidates
Database
For the core platform we can use a common relational database such as Postgres or Microsoft SQL. These options provide enough flexibility and functionality that the business will likely not need to make any major upgrades during its lifespan or be limited by the database technology.
Core API
The performance requirements for this service are quite low. Client's and end users will likely tolerate very slow server speeds, so the dev team doesn’t need to commit to an extremely high performance programming language or server technology.
The major concern is scalability, so we need to be careful to select a programming language and platform that can handle multi threading on the incoming requests handling.
Cloud hosting
Cloud hosting is quite common place and selecting a hosting provider is quite straight forward. AWS, GCP, Azure are all viable candidates.
User Interface
The user interface will require three different components:
Desktop web interface for the the companies/clients to register their poll and review the results. This is best developed use one of the popular frontend frameworks such as ReactJS, Angular or Vue
Mobile app and website for the voters to cast their vote. While most companies would prefer that users can vote from both web and mobile app, it is critical that we only enable the mobile app to ensure the security of the cryptographic tools.
Web interface (mobile and desktop) for public users to review the results of a poll, and explore the blockchain to verify the security of the vote.

Technology - Cryptography
Function
Candidates
Cryptographic Technology
The algorithms that make the voting process secure, anonymous and verifiable are not at all trivial to develop. This is a novel use of SK-SNARK technology, as such there are no off-the-shelf products available for use. 
Proven (Raposa) is a very clever startup in the EU who have developed very similar technology for a similar purpose. I believe the would be an ideal partner in this venture.
Blockchain hosting
Project Management
Learning tools

